{"type":"text","timestamp":1775884652812,"sessionID":"ses_28507b744ffedyI6Nh0umof18H","part":{"id":"prt_d7af86f22001dwVFDSugLLnk3D","messageID":"msg_d7af854fb001go61hg4B0fEmX5","sessionID":"ses_28507b744ffedyI6Nh0umof18H","type":"text","text":"Now I'll create the `design.md` file for the PCAP Analyzer Example Application based on the provided requirements and SDK design.","time":{"start":1775884652811,"end":1775884652811}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884652817,"sessionID":"ses_28507b744ffedyI6Nh0umof18H","part":{"id":"prt_d7af87565001uZ5YLnwbPFOdsZ","messageID":"msg_d7af854fb001go61hg4B0fEmX5","sessionID":"ses_28507b744ffedyI6Nh0umof18H","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_ab71d029227045088a14752c","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# PCAP еҲҶжһҗеҷЁзӨәдҫӢеә”з”Ё вҖ” Design\n\n**AR:** AR-037  \n**Module:** example  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n## Overview\n\nA PCAP (Packet Capture) analyzer example application that demonstrates the AgentCube SDK capabilities by analyzing network packet capture files using the Code Interpreter. The application uploads PCAP files to a remote code interpreter session, runs analysis scripts (using `scapy` or `tshark`), and retrieves structured results.\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                    User / Caller                         в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                       в”Ӯ\n                       в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ              PcapAnalyzer (example app)                  в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ FileUploaderв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ ScriptRunner в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ ResultParser   в”Ӯ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ         в”Ӯ                в”Ӯ                   в”Ӯ          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ         в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ                          в–ј                              в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ              CodeInterpreterClient (SDK)                в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                           в”Ӯ\n                           в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ              AgentCube Platform                          в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ         в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ Control     в”Ӯв—„в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–әв”Ӯ Code Interpreter Pod     в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ Plane       в”Ӯ         в”Ӯ (scapy / tshark / python)в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ         в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### `PcapAnalysisResult`\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass PcapAnalysisResult:\n    \"\"\"Structured result from PCAP analysis.\"\"\"\n    file_name: str\n    total_packets: int\n    protocols: Dict[str, int]          # protocol name -> packet count\n    top_talkers: List[Tuple[str, int]] # (ip_address, packet_count)\n    duration_seconds: float\n    errors: List[str]                  # analysis warnings/errors\n```\n\n### `PcapAnalyzerConfig`\n\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass PcapAnalyzerConfig:\n    \"\"\"Configuration for the PCAP analyzer.\"\"\"\n    pcap_file_path: str                # local path to .pcap/.pcapng\n    analysis_script: str = \"default\"   # \"default\" | \"protocol_stats\" | \"flow_analysis\"\n    output_format: str = \"json\"        # \"json\" | \"text\"\n    timeout: float = 120.0             # execution timeout in seconds\n```\n\n## Components\n\n### `PcapAnalyzer` (main class)\n\n```python\nclass PcapAnalyzer:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        config: PcapAnalyzerConfig,\n        sdk_client: Optional[CodeInterpreterClient] = None,\n    ): ...\n\n    def analyze(self) -> PcapAnalysisResult: ...\n    def _upload_pcap(self) -> str: ...           # returns remote path\n    def _get_analysis_script(self) -> str: ...   # returns Python script source\n    def _run_analysis(self, remote_path: str) -> str: ...  # returns raw output\n    def _parse_result(self, raw: str) -> PcapAnalysisResult: ...\n```\n\n### Analysis Scripts (embedded templates)\n\n#### Default Script (`default`)\n\n```python\n\"\"\"\nDefault PCAP analysis script executed in the remote Code Interpreter.\nUses scapy to extract packet statistics.\n\"\"\"\nfrom scapy.all import rdpcap, IP, TCP, UDP, ICMP\nimport json\nimport sys\n\ndef analyze_pcap(pcap_path):\n    packets = rdpcap(pcap_path)\n    \n    result = {\n        \"file_name\": pcap_path,\n        \"total_packets\": len(packets),\n        \"protocols\": {},\n        \"top_talkers\": [],\n        \"duration_seconds\": 0.0,\n        \"errors\": []\n    }\n    \n    # Protocol distribution\n    proto_counts = {\"TCP\": 0, \"UDP\": 0, \"ICMP\": 0, \"Other\": 0}\n    ip_counts = {}\n    first_ts = None\n    last_ts = None\n    \n    for pkt in packets:\n        ts = float(pkt.time)\n        if first_ts is None:\n            first_ts = ts\n        last_ts = ts\n        \n        if pkt.haslayer(IP):\n            src = pkt[IP].src\n            ip_counts[src] = ip_counts.get(src, 0) + 1\n        \n        if pkt.haslayer(TCP):\n            proto_counts[\"TCP\"] += 1\n        elif pkt.haslayer(UDP):\n            proto_counts[\"UDP\"] += 1\n        elif pkt.haslayer(ICMP):\n            proto_counts[\"ICMP\"] += 1\n        else:\n            proto_counts[\"Other\"] += 1\n    \n    result[\"protocols\"] = proto_counts\n    result[\"top_talkers\"] = sorted(\n        ip_counts.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True\n    )[:10]\n    result[\"duration_seconds\"] = (last_ts - first_ts) if first_ts and last_ts else 0.0\n    \n    return result\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    pcap_file = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) > 1 else \"/tmp/uploaded.pcap\"\n    print(json.dumps(analyze_pcap(pcap_file), indent=2))\n```\n\n#### Protocol Stats Script (`protocol_stats`)\n\nExtended version with per-protocol byte counts and port distribution.\n\n#### Flow Analysis Script (`flow_analysis`)\n\nExtracts unique flows (src_ip:src_port -> dst_ip:dst_port) with packet/byte counts.\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### `PcapAnalyzer.analyze()`\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|--------|--------|\n| Input | `PcapAnalyzerConfig` with valid `pcap_file_path` |\n| Output | `PcapAnalysisResult` dataclass |\n| Errors | `FileNotFoundError` if pcap doesn't exist; `CommandExecutionError` if remote execution fails; `ValueError` if result parsing fails |\n\n### Flow\n\n1. **Initialize SDK client** вҖ” Create or reuse `CodeInterpreterClient` (context manager)\n2. **Upload PCAP** вҖ” `client.upload_file(local_path, \"/tmp/analysis.pcap\")`\n3. **Upload analysis script** вҖ” `client.write_file(script_source, \"/tmp/analyze.py\")`\n4. **Execute** вҖ” `client.execute_command(\"python3 /tmp/analyze.py /tmp/analysis.pcap\", timeout=config.timeout)`\n5. **Parse** вҖ” Deserialize JSON output into `PcapAnalysisResult`\n6. **Cleanup** вҖ” Context manager `__exit__` handles session teardown\n\n## Error Handling\n\n| Error | Source | Handling |\n|-------|--------|----------|\n| PCAP file not found | Local filesystem | Raise `FileNotFoundError` with path |\n| Upload failure | SDK `upload_file` | Propagate SDK exception |\n| Script execution timeout | Remote PicoD | `CommandExecutionError` (exit 124) |\n| Script runtime error | Remote Python | `CommandExecutionError` with stderr |\n| Invalid JSON output | Parse phase | `ValueError(\"Failed to parse analysis result: ...\")` |\n| Empty PCAP file | Analysis script | Return result with `total_packets=0` |\n| Corrupted PCAP | scapy `rdpcap` | Script catches, reports in `errors` list |\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Test | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `test_parse_valid_result` | Parse valid JSON output into `PcapAnalysisResult` |\n| `test_parse_empty_packets` | Handle zero-packet PCAP gracefully |\n| `test_parse_malformed_json` | Raise `ValueError` on invalid JSON |\n| `test_get_analysis_script_default` | Default script contains required imports and function |\n| `test_config_defaults` | `PcapAnalyzerConfig` defaults are correct |\n\n### Integration Tests (require SDK + AgentCube platform)\n\n| Test | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `test_full_analysis_cycle` | Upload small PCAP вҶ’ analyze вҶ’ verify result structure |\n| `test_large_pcap_timeout` | Verify timeout handling with large files |\n| `test_corrupted_pcap` | Verify error reporting for invalid PCAP |\n| `test_protocol_stats_script` | Protocol stats script returns correct distribution |\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n- `tests/fixtures/small.pcap` вҖ” 10 packets (TCP/UDP/ICMP mix)\n- `tests/fixtures/empty.pcap` вҖ” Valid header, 0 packets\n- `tests/fixtures/corrupted.pcap` вҖ” Invalid file content\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Runtime (example app)\n\n```toml\ndependencies = [\n    \"agentcube-sdk\",  # from local path or published\n]\n```\n\n- No `scapy` dependency in the example app itself вҖ” analysis runs remotely in the Code Interpreter where `scapy` is pre-installed.\n\n### Test dependencies\n\n```toml\n[project.optional-dependencies]\ndev = [\n    \"pytest>=7.0\",\n    \"pytest-asyncio\",\n]\n```\n\n## File Layout\n\n```\nexample/pcap-analyzer/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ pyproject.toml\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ pcap_analyzer/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ __init__.py\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ analyzer.py          # PcapAnalyzer, PcapAnalysisResult, PcapAnalyzerConfig\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ scripts/\nв”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ __init__.py\nв”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ default.py       # Default analysis script template\nв”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ protocol_stats.py\nв”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ flow_analysis.py\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ examples/\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ quick_start.py       # Usage example\nв””в”Җв”Җ tests/\n    в”ңв”Җв”Җ __init__.py\n    в”ңв”Җв”Җ test_analyzer.py\n    в”ңв”Җв”Җ test_scripts.py\n    в””в”Җв”Җ fixtures/\n        в”ңв”Җв”Җ small.pcap\n        в”ңв”Җв”Җ empty.pcap\n        в””в”Җв”Җ corrupted.pcap\n```\n\n## Usage Example\n\n```python\nfrom pcap_analyzer import PcapAnalyzer, PcapAnalyzerConfig\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\nconfig = PcapAnalyzerConfig(\n    pcap_file_path=\"./captures/network.pcap\",\n    analysis_script=\"default\",\n    timeout=180.0,\n)\n\nwith CodeInterpreterClient(name=\"pcap-analyzer\") as client:\n    analyzer = PcapAnalyzer(config=config, sdk_client=client)\n    result = analyzer.analyze()\n    \n    print(f\"Total packets: {result.total_packets}\")\n    print(f\"Protocols: {result.protocols}\")\n    print(f\"Top talkers: {result.top_talkers[:5]}\")\n    print(f\"Duration: {result.duration_seconds:.2f}s\")\n```\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775884652806,"end":1775884652814}}}}
