{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884770954,"sessionID":"ses_28507b744ffedyI6Nh0umof18H","part":{"id":"prt_d7af9b01f001yWaIDPkheJykzp","messageID":"msg_d7af99713001RppzA05DHIISr7","sessionID":"ses_28507b744ffedyI6Nh0umof18H","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_34b68feac0db4fd4a92b17e5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-037: PCAP еҲҶжһҗеҷЁзӨәдҫӢеә”з”Ё вҖ” Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers the PCAP (Packet Capture) analyzer example application for the AgentCube Python SDK. It demonstrates the complete workflow of file upload, remote code execution, and result download using `CodeInterpreterClient`, providing users with a runnable network analysis reference implementation.\n\n### 1.2 System Context\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                         User / Developer                             в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ              examples/pcap_analyzer/                         в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ              pcap_analyzer.py                         в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ         (CLI Example Script)                          в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ                         в”Ӯ                                   в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ         CodeInterpreterClient (SDK)                   в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ   (upload_file, run_code, execute_command,            в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ    download_file, list_files, context manager)        в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n                             в”Ӯ\n                             в–ј\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                    AgentCube Platform                                в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ          в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  Control Plane       в”Ӯв—„в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–әв”Ӯ  Code Interpreter Pod      в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  (Session Lifecycle) в”Ӯ         в”Ӯ  (Python 3.10+, scapy)     в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ          в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n### 1.3 Design Principles\n\n- **Example-only**: No modifications to SDK core code; uses only public API (`__all__` exports)\n- **CLI script style**: Consistent with existing examples (`basic_usage.py`, `agent_runtime_usage.py`)\n- **Self-contained**: Single script with embedded analysis logic via `run_code`\n- **Graceful degradation**: `tshark` as optional enhancement with conditional detection\n- **Small footprint**: Sample PCAP < 1MB, no chunked upload complexity\n\n### 1.4 Package Structure\n\n```\nsdk-python/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ examples/\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ basic_usage.py                      # Existing\nв”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ agent_runtime_usage.py              # Existing\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ pcap_analyzer/                      # NEW (this AR)\nв”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ pcap_analyzer.py                # Main example script\nв”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ README.md                       # Usage guide\nв”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ requirements.txt                # Example dependencies\nв”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ sample_traffic.pcap             # Sample PCAP file (< 1MB)\nв””в”Җв”Җ ...\n```\n\n### 1.5 Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Scope | Purpose |\n|------------|-------|---------|\n| `agentcube-sdk` | Local import | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n| `scapy` | Remote sandbox | PCAP parsing (installed via `run_code` if needed) |\n| `tshark` (optional) | Remote sandbox | CLI filtering tool (conditional detection) |\n\n**No new Python package dependencies** вҖ” the example script uses only stdlib + `agentcube-sdk`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Analysis Result Format (JSON)\n\nThe remote analysis script produces JSON output with the following structure:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"file_name\": \"sample_traffic.pcap\",\n  \"total_packets\": 1234,\n  \"duration_seconds\": 60.5,\n  \"protocols\": {\n    \"TCP\": 800,\n    \"UDP\": 300,\n    \"ICMP\": 50,\n    \"HTTP\": 60,\n    \"DNS\": 24\n  },\n  \"top_source_ips\": [\n    {\"ip\": \"192.168.1.100\", \"count\": 500},\n    {\"ip\": \"10.0.0.1\", \"count\": 300}\n  ],\n  \"top_dest_ips\": [\n    {\"ip\": \"8.8.8.8\", \"count\": 200},\n    {\"ip\": \"1.1.1.1\", \"count\": 150}\n  ],\n  \"timeline\": [\n    {\"timestamp\": 1699000000.0, \"packets\": 100},\n    {\"timestamp\": 1699000010.0, \"packets\": 150}\n  ],\n  \"errors\": []\n}\n```\n\n### 2.2 CLI Arguments\n\n| Argument | Type | Default | Description |\n|----------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--pcap-file` | `str` | `sample_traffic.pcap` | Path to PCAP file to analyze |\n| `--output` | `str` | `analysis_result.json` | Local path for result output |\n| `--top-n` | `int` | `10` | Number of top IPs to report |\n| `--timeline-interval` | `float` | `10.0` | Timeline bucket size in seconds |\n| `--verbose` | `flag` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n\n### 2.3 Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Description |\n|----------|----------|-------------|\n| `ROUTER_URL` | Yes | Router endpoint URL |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | No | Control plane URL (defaults to SDK default) |\n| `AUTH_TOKEN` | No | Auth token (falls back to SA token file) |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Interfaces\n\n### 3.1 Main Script Entry Point\n\n```python\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"PCAP Analyzer Example вҖ” demonstrates CodeInterpreterClient workflow.\"\"\"\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport os\nimport sys\n\nfrom agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"PCAP Analyzer Example\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--pcap-file\", default=\"sample_traffic.pcap\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--output\", default=\"analysis_result.json\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--top-n\", type=int, default=10)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--timeline-interval\", type=float, default=10.0)\n    parser.add_argument(\"--verbose\", action=\"store_true\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    router_url = os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n    if not router_url:\n        print(\"Error: ROUTER_URL environment variable is required\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    analyze_pcap(\n        pcap_file=args.pcap_file,\n        output_file=args.output,\n        top_n=args.top_n,\n        timeline_interval=args.timeline_interval,\n        verbose=args.verbose,\n        router_url=router_url,\n    )\n```\n\n### 3.2 Core Analysis Function\n\n```python\ndef analyze_pcap(\n    pcap_file: str,\n    output_file: str,\n    top_n: int,\n    timeline_interval: float,\n    verbose: bool,\n    router_url: str,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Upload PCAP, run analysis, download results.\"\"\"\n```\n\n**Workflow:**\n\n1. Validate PCAP file exists locally\n2. Create `CodeInterpreterClient` (context manager)\n3. Upload PCAP file to remote sandbox (`upload_file`)\n4. Install `scapy` if needed (`run_code` with `pip install`)\n5. Execute analysis script (`run_code` with embedded Python)\n6. Optionally run `tshark` commands (`execute_command` if available)\n7. Write results to remote file (`write_file` or script output)\n8. Download results (`download_file`)\n9. Print summary to console\n10. Context manager cleanup (`__exit__` вҶ’ `stop()`)\n\n### 3.3 Embedded Analysis Script (via `run_code`)\n\nThe analysis logic is passed as a Python string to `run_code`. It uses `scapy` to parse the PCAP file:\n\n```python\nANALYSIS_SCRIPT = \"\"\"\nfrom scapy.all import rdpcap, IP, TCP, UDP, ICMP, DNS, Raw\nimport json\nimport sys\nfrom collections import Counter\n\ndef analyze_pcap(pcap_path, top_n=10, timeline_interval=10.0):\n    packets = rdpcap(pcap_path)\n    \n    result = {\n        \"file_name\": pcap_path,\n        \"total_packets\": len(packets),\n        \"duration_seconds\": 0.0,\n        \"protocols\": {},\n        \"top_source_ips\": [],\n        \"top_dest_ips\": [],\n        \"timeline\": [],\n        \"errors\": []\n    }\n    \n    if not packets:\n        return result\n    \n    # Duration\n    first_ts = float(packets[0].time)\n    last_ts = float(packets[-1].time)\n    result[\"duration_seconds\"] = last_ts - first_ts\n    \n    # Protocol distribution\n    proto_counts = Counter()\n    src_ips = Counter()\n    dst_ips = Counter()\n    timeline_buckets = Counter()\n    \n    for pkt in packets:\n        ts = float(pkt.time)\n        bucket = int((ts - first_ts) / timeline_interval) * timeline_interval + first_ts\n        \n        if pkt.haslayer(TCP):\n            proto_counts[\"TCP\"] += 1\n            if pkt.haslayer(Raw):\n                proto_counts[\"HTTP\"] += 1  # Simplified HTTP detection\n        elif pkt.haslayer(UDP):\n            if pkt.haslayer(DNS):\n                proto_counts[\"DNS\"] += 1\n            else:\n                proto_counts[\"UDP\"] += 1\n        elif pkt.haslayer(ICMP):\n            proto_counts[\"ICMP\"] += 1\n        else:\n            proto_counts[\"Other\"] += 1\n        \n        if pkt.haslayer(IP):\n            src_ips[pkt[IP].src] += 1\n            dst_ips[pkt[IP].dst] += 1\n        \n        timeline_buckets[bucket] += 1\n    \n    result[\"protocols\"] = dict(proto_counts)\n    result[\"top_source_ips\"] = [\n        {\"ip\": ip, \"count\": count}\n        for ip, count in src_ips.most_common(top_n)\n    ]\n    result[\"top_dest_ips\"] = [\n        {\"ip\": ip, \"count\": count}\n        for ip, count in dst_ips.most_common(top_n)\n    ]\n    result[\"timeline\"] = sorted([\n        {\"timestamp\": ts, \"packets\": count}\n        for ts, count in timeline_buckets.items()\n    ], key=lambda x: x[\"timestamp\"])\n    \n    return result\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    pcap_file = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) > 1 else \"/tmp/uploaded.pcap\"\n    top_n = int(sys.argv[2]) if len(sys.argv) > 2 else 10\n    interval = float(sys.argv[3]) if len(sys.argv) > 3 else 10.0\n    \n    result = analyze_pcap(pcap_file, top_n, interval)\n    print(json.dumps(result, indent=2))\n\"\"\"\n```\n\n### 3.4 Optional tshark Enhancement\n\n```python\ndef check_tshark_available(client: CodeInterpreterClient) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Check if tshark is available in the remote sandbox.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        result = client.execute_command(\"which tshark\")\n        return result.strip() != \"\"\n    except Exception:\n        return False\n\n\ndef run_tshark_filter(client: CodeInterpreterClient, pcap_path: str, filter_expr: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Run tshark with a display filter on the remote PCAP.\"\"\"\n    cmd = f\"tshark -r {pcap_path} -Y '{filter_expr}' -T fields -e ip.src -e ip.dst -e frame.len\"\n    return client.execute_command(cmd)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Error Classification\n\n| Scenario | Exception | Handling |\n|----------|-----------|----------|\n| PCAP file not found locally | `FileNotFoundError` | Print error, exit 1 |\n| `ROUTER_URL` not set | `ValueError` | Print error, exit 1 |\n| Upload failure | SDK exception | Propagate with context |\n| `scapy` installation failure | `CommandExecutionError` | Retry or warn, continue |\n| Analysis script error | `CommandExecutionError` | Print stderr, exit 1 |\n| Result download failure | SDK exception | Propagate with context |\n| Invalid JSON output | `json.JSONDecodeError` | Print raw output, warn |\n| Context manager cleanup failure | SDK exception | Log warning, exit |\n\n### 4.2 Error Recovery Strategy\n\n```python\ndef analyze_pcap(...):\n    # Pre-flight checks\n    if not os.path.exists(pcap_file):\n        print(f\"Error: PCAP file not found: {pcap_file}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    # Context manager ensures cleanup\n    with CodeInterpreterClient(\n        name=\"pcap-analyzer\",\n        router_url=router_url,\n        verbose=verbose,\n    ) as client:\n        try:\n            # Upload\n            remote_path = f\"/tmp/{os.path.basename(pcap_file)}\"\n            client.upload_file(pcap_file, remote_path)\n            \n            # Install scapy (best effort)\n            try:\n                client.run_code(\"python\", \"import scapy\")\n            except Exception:\n                if verbose:\n                    print(\"Installing scapy in remote sandbox...\")\n                client.run_code(\"python\", \"import subprocess; subprocess.run(['pip', 'install', 'scapy'])\")\n            \n            # Run analysis\n            script = ANALYSIS_SCRIPT.replace(\"TOP_N_PLACEHOLDER\", str(top_n))\n            result_json = client.run_code(\"python\", script)\n            result = json.loads(result_json)\n            \n            # Optional tshark\n            if check_tshark_available(client):\n                tshark_result = run_tshark_filter(client, remote_path, \"tcp\")\n                result[\"tshark_tcp_summary\"] = tshark_result\n            \n            # Save results locally\n            with open(output_file, \"w\") as f:\n                json.dump(result, f, indent=2)\n            \n            # Print summary\n            print_analysis_summary(result)\n            \n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"Analysis failed: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n            sys.exit(1)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Implementation Notes\n\n### 5.1 Remote Sandbox Assumptions\n\n| Assumption | Verification | Fallback |\n|------------|--------------|----------|\n| Python 3.10+ available | `run_code(\"python\", \"import sys; print(sys.version)\")` | Error if not met |\n| `pip install` works | Try `pip install scapy` | Pre-install in sandbox image |\n| `/tmp` writable | `execute_command(\"touch /tmp/test && rm /tmp/test\")` | Use alternative path |\n| `tshark` available (optional) | `execute_command(\"which tshark\")` | Skip tshark features |\n\n### 5.2 Script Size Considerations\n\nThe embedded `ANALYSIS_SCRIPT` is ~60 lines of Python. For `run_code`, this is passed as a string argument. If the script grows significantly, consider:\n\n1. Using `write_file` to upload the script first, then `execute_command` to run it\n2. Splitting into multiple `run_code` calls\n\nCurrent approach (inline) is preferred for simplicity and demonstration purposes.\n\n### 5.3 Timeout Configuration\n\n| Operation | Timeout | Rationale |\n|-----------|---------|-----------|\n| PCAP upload | Default (120s) | < 1MB file, should be fast |\n| scapy install | 60s | Network-dependent |\n| Analysis execution | 120s | Depends on PCAP size |\n| tshark filter | 60s | Optional enhancement |\n| Result download | Default (120s) | JSON output, small |\n\n### 5.4 Sample PCAP Generation\n\nThe `sample_traffic.pcap` file can be generated using `scapy`:\n\n```python\n# scripts/generate_sample_pcap.py\nfrom scapy.all import IP, TCP, UDP, ICMP, wrpcap, Ether\nimport random\n\npackets = []\nbase_time = 1699000000.0\n\nfor i in range(100):\n    src = f\"192.168.1.{random.randint(1, 254)}\"\n    dst = f\"10.0.0.{random.randint(1, 254)}\"\n    \n    if i % 3 == 0:\n        pkt = IP(src=src, dst=dst) / TCP(sport=random.randint(1024, 65535), dport=80)\n    elif i % 3 == 1:\n        pkt = IP(src=src, dst=dst) / UDP(sport=53, dport=random.randint(1024, 65535))\n    else:\n        pkt = IP(src=src, dst=dst) / ICMP()\n    \n    pkt.time = base_time + i * 0.5\n    packets.append(pkt)\n\nwrpcap(\"sample_traffic.pcap\", packets)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Testing Strategy\n\n### 6.1 Test Categories\n\n| Category | Scope | Approach |\n|----------|-------|----------|\n| Script validation | Syntax, imports | `python -m py_compile pcap_analyzer.py` |\n| Unit tests | Analysis logic | Run embedded script locally with test PCAP |\n| Integration tests | SDK interaction | Mock `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n| Manual E2E | Full workflow | Run against real AgentCube platform |\n\n### 6.2 Key Test Scenarios\n\n| Test Name | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `test_script_syntax` | Embedded analysis script compiles without errors |\n| `test_analysis_with_sample_pcap` | Run analysis on sample_traffic.pcap, verify JSON structure |\n| `test_empty_pcap` | Handle PCAP with 0 packets gracefully |\n| `test_cli_argument_parsing` | Verify argparse handles all flags correctly |\n| `test_missing_router_url` | Exit with error if ROUTER_URL not set |\n| `test_missing_pcap_file` | Exit with error if PCAP file not found |\n| `test_mocked_sdk_workflow` | Mock CodeInterpreterClient, verify call sequence |\n\n### 6.3 Mocked SDK Test Example\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\n\ndef test_mocked_sdk_workflow():\n    \"\"\"Verify the expected SDK call sequence.\"\"\"\n    mock_client = MagicMock()\n    mock_client.__enter__ = MagicMock(return_value=mock_client)\n    mock_client.__exit__ = MagicMock(return_value=False)\n    \n    mock_client.run_code.return_value = json.dumps({\n        \"total_packets\": 100,\n        \"protocols\": {\"TCP\": 60, \"UDP\": 40},\n        \"top_source_ips\": [],\n        \"top_dest_ips\": [],\n        \"timeline\": [],\n        \"errors\": []\n    })\n    \n    with patch(\"agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient\", return_value=mock_client):\n        # Run analyze_pcap with test fixtures\n        # Verify call sequence:\n        # 1. upload_file called\n        # 2. run_code called for analysis\n        # 3. download_file or result handling\n        pass\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Usage Examples\n\n### 7.1 Basic Usage\n\n```bash\nexport ROUTER_URL=\"http://router:8080\"\ncd examples/pcap_analyzer\npython pcap_analyzer.py --pcap-file sample_traffic.pcap\n```\n\n**Expected output:**\n\n```\nPCAP Analysis Complete\n=====================\nFile: sample_traffic.pcap\nTotal packets: 100\nDuration: 49.50s\n\nProtocol Distribution:\n  TCP:  60 (60.0%)\n  UDP:  40 (40.0%)\n\nTop Source IPs:\n  192.168.1.105: 15 packets\n  192.168.1.200: 12 packets\n  192.168.1.50:  10 packets\n\nTop Destination IPs:\n  10.0.0.1: 25 packets\n  10.0.0.5: 20 packets\n\nResults saved to: analysis_result.json\n```\n\n### 7.2 Custom Parameters\n\n```bash\npython pcap_analyzer.py \\\n  --pcap-file /path/to/capture.pcap \\\n  --output /path/to/report.json \\\n  --top-n 20 \\\n  --timeline-interval 5.0 \\\n  --verbose\n```\n\n### 7.3 With tshark (if available)\n\nWhen `tshark` is detected in the remote sandbox, additional filtering output is included:\n\n```\ntshark TCP Filter Results:\n  192.168.1.100 -> 10.0.0.1: 1500 bytes\n  192.168.1.100 -> 10.0.0.1: 1200 bytes\n  ...\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. README Content\n\nThe `examples/pcap_analyzer/README.md` will contain:\n\n```markdown\n# PCAP Analyzer Example\n\nDemonstrates the complete CodeInterpreterClient workflow:\nupload вҶ’ analyze вҶ’ download.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Python 3.10+\n- `agentcube-sdk` installed\n- Access to AgentCube platform (ROUTER_URL)\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```bash\nexport ROUTER_URL=\"http://router:8080\"\npython pcap_analyzer.py --pcap-file sample_traffic.pcap\n```\n\n## Analysis Features\n\n- Protocol distribution (TCP/UDP/ICMP/DNS/HTTP)\n- Top N source and destination IPs\n- Traffic timeline overview\n- Optional tshark filtering (if available in sandbox)\n\n## Output\n\nResults are saved as JSON and printed as a summary to stdout.\n```\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/design.md","time":{"start":1775884770933,"end":1775884770952}}}}
